news.description: Chris Cornell, former frontman of Soundgarden and Audioslave, passed away May 17, 2017 in Detroit at the age of 52. In light of his passing, we are republishing this early feature with Soundgarden, which originally appeared in the December 1989 issue of Spin.  They're Axl's favorite band, one of the 150 or so that Ian Astbury loves and hopes to produce, and the folks Mark Lanegan of the Screaming Trees calls "four guys who wear clothes." Soundgarden are all meat and hair and ripped knees, the band most likely to succeed from the Seattle scene. Spread out on the long beige-plaid couch on the long porch of a huge, old, white house, they are drinking Budweiser and talking about what to do this evening. "So, are we gonna play tonight or not?" guitarist Kim Thayil asks. news.description: Ruthless Harry Kane struck four goals as Tottenham dismantled Leicester 6-1.  The England forward's haul moved him two ahead of Romelu Lukaku in the race for the Premier League's golden boot with 26 goals ahead of Sunday's season-finale at Hull. Son Heung-min also scored twice at the King Power Stadium as Spurs continued to shrug off any disappointment following Chelsea's title win. The visitors were untouchable as they sealed their 13th win in their last 16 games in all competitions, having already cemented second place.
news.title: Leicester 1-6 Tottenham: Harry Kane bags four goals to take charge of Golden Boot race

news.author: talkSPORT
news.description: Tottenham boss Mauricio Pochettino labelled Harry Kane one of the best strikers in the world after he hit four in Spurs' rout of Leicester. The England forward is now in pole position to defend the golden boot after his haul in Tottenham's 6-1 win at the King Power Stadium.  He is two goals ahead of Everton's Romelu Lukaku on 26 heading into the final weekend of the season with Spurs travelling to Hull and Everton going to Arsenal.
news.title: Tottenham FC news: Mauricio Pochettino hails Harry Kane as one of the best strikers in the world after stunning four-goal display
